# Context menu dividers

Project-wide pattern for **`q-menu`** / **`q-btn-dropdown`** panels with **`q-list`** + **`q-item`** action rows.

Canonical renderer: **`AppControlSingleMenu`**. Playbook: [fantasia-context-menu-dividers skill](../skills/fantasia-context-menu-dividers/SKILL.md).

## Two divider tiers

| Tier | When | Style |
| --- | --- | --- |
| **Group separator** | Logical section break (browse Ôćĺ actions, close Ôćĺ destructive, duplicate Ôćĺ delete, expand block Ôćĺ add-new) | **`$appControlMenus-separatorColor`** (**`primary-bright`**), height **`$appControlSingleMenu-separator-height`** (0.5px), full opacity |
| **separatorAlt** | Between consecutive items in same group with no group separator above | **`$appControlMenus-separatorAltColor`** (**`text-menu-separator`**), same height, **`opacity: 0.2`** |

**Never** stack group separator + separatorAlt on the same boundary.

## Placement rule

Before each item row at index **Ôëą 1**:

- Previous row was **group separator** Ôćĺ **no** separatorAlt
- Previous row was another **item** Ôćĺ **yes** separatorAlt
- First row Ôćĺ **no** divider

Data-driven menus: **`contextMenuShouldShowSeparatorAltBeforeItem`** in **`AppControlMenus/scripts/functions/contextMenuShouldShowSeparatorAltBeforeItem.ts`**.

Hand-built **`v-for`**: **`v-if="contextMenuShouldShowSeparatorAltBeforeIndex(index)"`** (or **`index > 0`** when no inline group separators in loop).

## SCSS

**`@use`** mixin from **`AppControlMenus/styles/_contextMenuSeparators.mixin.scss`**:

- **`@include fa-context-menu-separator-group`** on **`*__separator`**
- **`@include fa-context-menu-separator-alt`** on **`*__separatorAlt`**

Feature BEM block keeps local class names; tokens stay shared.

## Themed exceptions

- **Light** menus (e.g. **`GlobalLanguageSelector`**) ÔÇö same alt rule; alt color from feature **`styles/_variables.scss`** (often **`text-menu-separator`** + **`opacity: 0.2`**).
- **Splash** resume dropdown ÔÇö same alt rule; splash-specific alt token in feature SCSS.
- **Destructive sub-boundary** (e.g. force-close Ôćĺ delete) may use explicit **`primary-bright`** class when product calls for emphasis ÔÇö not separatorAlt.

## Not in scope

**`q-color`**, icon grid pickers, locale translation field panels, confirm-only **`q-menu`** shells without action **`q-item`** rows.

